Frederick King (21 November 1850 – 16 June 1893) was an English amateur cricketer who played one first-class cricket match for Kent County Cricket Club in 1871.
King was born at Harbledown in Kent in 1850 and died at Hammersmith in London in 1893 aged 42. His only first-class match was against Sussex in June 1871. He is also known to have played one match for the amateur Gentlemen of Kent side in the same year.
